<hr size=1> /em unsheathes her Soulfire and composes herself to speak...<br><br>I'm afraid I have lost heart as a Paladin.  I gained this majestic weapon 17 crusades ago and today I finally have confronted what I didn't want to say about it: our beautiful holy sword is not fit for purpose.  With the maturity of Norrath's economy, Soulfire is now better suited to Paladins in our 30s, rather than our mid-40s when most of us complete the arduous quest.<br><br>In truth, I keep Soulfire on me as a beacon of light to guide parties through dark places.  My friends tell me they can see me from a mile off.  Isn't this degrading?  How could such a beautiful weapon become so neglected?<br><br>/em visibly musters determination and renewed clarity before continuing ...<br><br>I have decided to do something about it and I need your help.  If you feel the same way I do about needing to realign the damage capacity of Soulfire with the levels of those attaining the weapon, would you please take 2 minutes to execute a /feedback next time you log in.  All you need to do is write a couple of heart-felt sentences about why you think Soulfire needs a bit more bite.<br><br>Thank you.<br>/bow <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1222<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/24/01 11:31:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.champions-eternal.net/Luthair.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire - great for leading your party through dark pla</span><hr size=1> It wasn't that spectacular pre-RoK either. <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?6318">Luthair Paendrag</a></b><br>Level 4 Cavalier<br><a href="http://www.champions-eternal.net">Champions Eternal</a><br>Tunare<br><img src="http://www.champions-eternal.net/begging.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvulkaneverheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulkan Everheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://molnir.pittbull.com/hammer.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/01 2:46:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire - great for leading your party through dark pla</span><hr size=1> Soulfire got its bigger bite by upgrade to FA, then FD..  <p><strong><font color=darkred>Vulkan Everheart</font><br><Font color=darkblue>Paladin of Mithaniel Marr</font></strong>"Warriors SCREAM for not having superiority""Hybrids PLEAD for Equallity"<br><a href=http://http://www.tunare-europa.co.uk/tide/target=_top><img src=http://www.btinternet.com/~andy.traynor/siggy/tide.jpg border=0></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrachan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drachan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/01 7:55:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=C:\Eigene WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire - great for leading your party through dark pla</span><hr size=1> THIS IS A COPY OF THREAD I STARETED EARLIER THIS MONTHS.<br>Btw, just because you a hard quest behind doesn't make this weapon any better. You could add a quest where any other blade that dropped of mobs could be base. This is somthing totally different. <br><br>___________________________________________________<br>Hello all,<br><br>I am probably not the first to mention it, but it keeps coming back to know inside my brain so I'll let it out.<br><br>Once upon a time, there was a Sword called Soulfire, received by paladins following a quest, and that simply looked marvelous to behold.<br>Paladins must have worn it with pride, and wielded as well. The DPS was lower than the Mithril 2hs considering the haste effect, but it had some stat boni as well, and a few heals.<br><br>Then came Kunark<br>Then came Velious<br>Then came more updates<br><br>Now, that beautiful sword to behold, not merely a random drop of the fruit of a one time raid, but connected to several minor quests, is but a shadow compared to the likes of the new weapons offered on the new continents (and even on the old)<br><br>Let's start my ranting with the Blackened Alloy Bastard Sword, the upgraded Black Iron Bastard Sword from Runnyeye.<br>With a dmg/del of 24/39 it beats the Soulfire on DPS and also is so common a drop and easy to farm that when compared to the quest needed for Soulfire it makes your jaw go slack.<br><br>I will mention the Shieldstorm, this blade now selling for 1 to 2kp is 22/43, with AC boni, and more including resist boni for all categories. The DPS is so close to Soulfire that it can be called equivalent on that aspect.<br><br>Th Arbitor's Combine 30/43 ratio simply sends Soulfire down to the torch level, not to mention much better WIS (15 vis 7) and mana or hp bonus.<br><br>The Throneblade of the Ykesha 33/51 buries the Soulfire, even more so with the new dmg bonus regulation. The str bonus is nearly as good (6 vs 7), not to mention the 75 DD proc.<br><br>I could go on and on.<br><br>I am just so disappointed. ATM I only use my Soulfire as a mana booster when acting as backup healer, and this is only because I wield a Throneblade of the Ykesha. Had I an Arbitor's Combine I'd just leave the Soulfire in my bank account.<br><br>I know Soulfire is only a step to the FA and FD, but still, it has been originally made to be more than that, and the graphics used on it reinforce this. Now it's good only to impress newbees...<br><br>I ask all fairly, shouldn't the Soulfire get a revamp in the light of the new direct loot and tradable blades from Kunark and Velious. It's so unfair to this weapon, to those doing the quest, and to the spirit of the game. What was the point of giving it such great looks if it's not even equivalent in DPS to a BABS that are sold for under 500pp some times (even know of one being given free)<br><br>IMHO the Soulfire should at least get the Dmg/Del ratio of an Arbitor Combine Greatsword (I saw sold for 3,5kp recently) if not better and/or some improvement on the boni (maybe some resists, Ac bonus and/or higher stat boni) and/or a minor proc.<br><br>That still would not make it an uber item. But atm it is just a decorative item, at beast a heavy torch. Sad, so very very sad.<br><br>Does anyone know if there is a request already in that sense, or a response on the side of the developers?<br><br>Thanks for infos and opinions<br>____________________________________________________<br><br><br> <p><div align="center"><font size="3"><i><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><b><font color="#CCCCCC">Drachan de Rocfaucon, the Silversword </font></b></font></i></font><br><b><font size="2">Cavalier of the Prime Healer</font> </b><br><b><i><font size="2">Member of the  <font face="blacc_.ttf" color="#FFCC00">Crusaders of Faith</font></font></i><font size="3"><br></font> </b> </div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukohinoornoblespirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kohinoor Noblespirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/27/01 1:53:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.everlore.com/GFILES/UserPic11082_6207.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire - great for leading your party through dark pla</span><hr size=1> Those of you who posted here seem pretty down on Soulfire, as am I.  Did you execute the /feedback command when you logged in today?  You may think the &quot;Power of One&quot; is insignificant, but the oceans began with a single droplet.  If you do nothing, then nothing will change.<br><br>When I answered the call to knighthood I never expected it to be easy.  Nor did I intend to just lie there and take the punishment.  Please, draw on your courage, your nobility, and your commitment to your class - use the /feedback process. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilfh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silfh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/27/01 9:02:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire - great for leading your party through dark pla</span><hr size=1> <br>Only comment I have is that of all my 2h weapons, Soulfire has the largest damage bonus (17).<br>My current 2her has a damage bonus of 12 (aged velium claidhmore). <p><table width="100%" align="center"><tr><td width="24%" align="left" valign="middle"><img src="http://members.home.net/craighuffnagle/silfh_pix.jpg" height="120" width="60"></td><td width="38%" align="right" valign="middle"><a href="mailto:silfh@eqcrosswinds.com">Silfh V'Ester<br></a><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Knight of 55 seasons<br></a>Servant of Tunare</td><td width="38%" align="left" valign="middle">Guild Leader<br><a href="http://www.eqcrosswinds.com">Court of the Crosswinds<br></a><a href="http://www.ralloszek.net">Rallos Zek<br></a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=normandy>Normandy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/15/01 4:12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soulfire</span><hr size=1> Something else that could help the Soulfire be more greatly appreciated would be a minor quest, or even just a &quot;trade-in&quot; to a particular NPC, which would recharge the 5 charges of Complete Healing.<br><br>Having 5 CH's per outing (until you could get back to the quest NPC for a recharge) would be a fine thing, yet hardly unbalance Paladins nor put any real bite on the Cleric's uber-healer monopoly.<br><br>Plus it would make us more welcome and useful on raids, always a good thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=normandy>Normandy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/15/01 4:14:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soulfire</span><hr size=1> Heh -- I love the RP presentation, Kohinoor... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 367<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/16/01 5:53:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulfire</span><hr size=1> A few things:<br><br>One, what with Soulfire being farmed by players competing in the Test of Tactics, I'm not at all desirous of there being a way for the Soulfire to be recharged.  That would just mean more NON-Paladins running around with a HOLY WEAPON in their backpack, healing themselves.  Uncool, and not very RP.<br><br>Two, I have never, ever, been interested in acquiring a Soulfire.  Because even as long as a year ago (right after Kunark came out), it was junk.  It's a holy weapon, yes, but as a weapon, it's junk.  Worthless, except for the 5 charges.  And as pointed out here, that is just plain darn WRONG.<br><br>What could be done to improve SoulFire without overpowering it?  Well, for starters, BANE damage against undead would be nice.  A LOT of it, say Bane Damage: 10 (this would add 10 to the weapons base damage against undead).  This would give 30th - 45th level paladins TWO weapons to use against undead, Ghoulbane (with its' Dismiss Undead proc) and Soulfire, which would become a 33dmg 45dly weapon.  Even still, 33/45 is only slightly better than an ACG.  But it would be an improvement.<br><br>What else could you do to Soulfire to improve it without overpowering it?  Well, adding BASH capability to it would be an improvement, certainly.  However, since it already has an effect, there's not much else that can be done other than increasing damage. <p>Aragir Lancot<BR>"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR><BR>Paladin of the 44th shield<BR>Exiles, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthorondar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorondar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/16/01 2:48:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tufts.edu/~soei01/thor-shirt2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hate to break it to ya</span><hr size=1> But as previously stated, Soulfire gets its &quot;bite&quot; by being an integral part of the FA quest, which then gets upgraded to FD.<br><br>It is not meant to be the end all be all of Paladin weapons.<br><br>Furthermore, when you get to the really end-game situations, you end up banking your FD (or maybe you keep it in your pack to show off or something) in favor of:<br><br>(Pick your choice)<br>Frostwrath<br>Emerald Bastardsword of Purity<br>Dawncaller<br>Primal 2handers<br>Primal Knights' Sword<br>Axe of Slaughter<br><br>Whatever else ToV puts in your lap.<br><br>For a mid-40's sort of a weapon, yes the Soulfire has other competitors but don't tell me you can loot one of those items besides the alloy stuff from Runney-eye on your own.  Even the Throneblade of Ykesha would be hard to get at mid-40's without a large raid crew of mid-40's...<br><br>It's not that bad, certainly I would still prefer Ghoulbane in favor of the shield at that level.<br><br> <p><small><i>Look at me standing here<br>Crying out my final tears<br>Look at me in the rain<br>Crying out your name</small></i><br><a href="mailto:Fletop@zombieworld.com">Thorondar Fury</a><br>Crusader <br><b><a href="http://www.watchers-brell.com">Watchers</a></b> - Brell Serilis<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11206">Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/19/01 12:40:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hate to break it to ya</span><hr size=1> Actually, I'm 45 now, and I'm wielding an Arbitors Combine Greatsword.  Miles and MILES better than a Soulfire.  No, I didn't loot it myself, but it was much easier to get.  And could I really get soulfire at this level?  Maybe, I don't know.  But certainly not without a lot of help from my guild and all the friends I have on Xegony.<br><br>What it all boils down to is that the soulfire quest has a serious Risk Vs. Reward imbalance.  Yeah, okay, so it gets used in the Fiery Avenger quest.  SO!?!?  That doesn't make Soulfire any better for your average paladin who doesn't have time to camp two dragons for rare book drops.  Verant has said over and over again that epic weapons are not intended to be available to your average player.<br><br>Saying that Soulfire &quot;gets its' bite by being a part of the FA quest&quot; is basically saying &quot;any paladin who doesn't intend to get an FA/FD should just not bother with Soulfire.&quot;  Well, that's really how it is right now anyway.  Heck, why bother getting soulfire before you have the two books and are ready to get FA, anyway?  I mean, it's junk.  It only &quot;gets its' bite by being a part of the FA quest&quot; so why have it if you aren't about to do the Fiery Avenger?<br><br>Oh.  Wait.  It has those 5 charges of Complete Heal.  And anybody can use them, even necros or SK's, and when all 5 charges are gone, they can give the Soulfire to their pet for show (you sure wouldn't want to give it to a pet for them to FIGHT with).<br><br>I think we've established that Soulfire is seriously less than what it should be.  Being a part of the Fiery Avenger quest doesn't make it any less inappropriate from a risk vs. reward standpoint.  Regardless of what weapon I will be wielding when I reach 60th level (2 years from now), I'm interested in seeing Soulfire be a more level- and risk-appropriate weapon than it is.  If you have much better gear, and don't need or want Soulfire improved, that's fine.  But its no reason to discourage a bunch of motivated Paladins from asking for a wrong to be righted.<br><br>EDIT:  Oh, and according to Copelands Weapon Analyzer (which is probably now out of date due to recent changes in 2h damage), Soulfire is about 50dpm behind a Black alloy Bastard sword at my level.  Imagine, a weapon that I can loot solo in a risk-free dungeon is better (except for the 5 charges of CH) than a weapon that would take several groups and several quests to acquire.  I guess if I was twinking an SK or a paladin, I'd get him both.  Soulfire for the CH charges, and the BABS to actually do damage. <p>Aragir Lancot<BR>"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR><BR>Paladin of the 45th shield<BR>Exiles, Xegony<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicPr