the sword loks so nice, it is just a sad joke that all you can use it for is a 5 charges CH potion...<br>I stay with the idea that the Soulfire should be upgraded to an AGCS (which still has more WIS and Mana if not Str anyway), and maybe have another little bonus.<br><br>The fact that you undertake such a long quest and cannot just buy it of a bored highbee in EC, that should justify the big improvement !!<br><br>No one will convince me otherwise. I now wield a piercing from DN which is much beter, and maybe soon get other nice weapon.<br>The fact is once we get to these weapons we highbee paladins forget about Soulfire. Just because we don't need it or are focused on much better stuff should not let us become blase.<br><br>Or Soulfire will end up becoming just a boring thing that you goddam have to go through so to get your FA. This is not what it should be, certainly not.<br> <p><div align="center"><font size="3"><i><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><b><font color="#CCCCCC">Drachan de Rocfaucon, the Silversword </font></b></font></i></font><br><b><font size="2">Cavalier of the Prime Healer</font> </b><br><b><i><font size="2">Member of the  <font face="blacc_.ttf" color="#FFCC00">Crusaders of Faith</font></font></i><font size="3"><br></font> </b> </div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 452<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/23/01 8:25:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Walk in the park</span><hr size=1> Once you become a highbee paladin. The actual acquisition of soulfire is very easy. The only pseudo difficult part is killing lucan and we've proven that it can be done solo at 60. And it's not hard to do with a couple 50+s. The only real camping time would be for xicotl which isn't that bad compared to alot of other camps these days. You can just pass through fp and kill lucan at your leisure. <br>I would say that the weapon is subpar since kunark/velious came out. But I would also say that acquiring the sword has become relatively trivialized since they came out as well. <br>It is a right of passage and you can take pride in the fact that only a paladin can wield it, but basically it is a quest for a 5 charge CH item. And that is very very valuable. The weapon itself sucks, the charges rock. <br>If they took away the CH charges, then there would be no reason whatsoever for someone to get it. It would become an item that epic wielding paladins had to quest for. that's it.<br>Possibly someone could twink out a lowbie pally with it, but basically it isn't even worth the effort for that, except for looks.<br>I haven't really bothered to finish mine yet, I have most of the items except for killing Lucan.  I don't think I'll be going for my epic any time soon, as I'll most likely default to the ND so it is just one of those things that will take up another inventory slot in the bank.<br>Unless they up the difficulty of acquiring it, they can't really justify upping the ratio of it.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 384<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/23/01 6:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Trivial for HIGH level paladins, maybe</span><hr size=1> But Soulfire certainly is NOT trivial for paladins lower than 50.  It certainly would not be trivial for me.  I remember a level 52 paladin in a guild I used to be in going for his soulfire.  He had about two groups of 50+ to help out.  How, please, is that &quot;EASY?&quot;<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Unless they up the difficulty of acquiring it, they can't really justify upping the ratio of it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Now, THAT is a bunch of crap, Bizomb.  You are looking at it as a level 60 paladin, and not as a paladin who could conceivably find it useful to WIELD SoulFire.  Just fix it so that the charges can only be used if the weapon is equipped, and you have every justification in the world to make it a better weapon.<br><br>Again, if you've got better stuff, thats great.  But it's no reason to come into this thread and claim that there's no justification for improving Soulfire.<br><br>Aragir Lancot<br>&quot;One man plus the truth equals a majority.&quot;<br><br>Exiles, Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uferok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ferok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/23/01 9:00:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ferok.freeservers.com/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trivial for HIGH level paladins, maybe</span><hr size=1> All i know is that I was damn proud to have one, and Im still glad i had one, or i couldnt wield this far prettier sword /giggle<br><br>...dwarfs dont giggle /sigh <p><center><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/alexjt724/ferok/ferok7.jpg"><br><a href="http://pub46.