ns would get the ability and it &quot;might&quot; not just sit in everyone's bank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 423<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/6/01 1:44:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Improve SoulFire!</span><hr size=1> /sigh<br><br>Please note that I do NOT advocate upping the ratio on SoulFire.  I am STRONGLY in favor of adding Bane damage vs Undead to it.  Somethign on the order of +10 Bane damage.<br><br>What with the new spells vs Undead, it seems very appropriate to me.<br><br> <p>Aragir Lancot<BR>"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR><BR>Paladin of the 45th shield<BR>Exiles, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirderekdrygon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Derek Drygon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/7/01 8:43:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://champions.morpheus.net/pics/derek2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Improve SoulFire!</span><hr size=1> I strongly disagree with soulfire getting an upgrade.  <br><br>I did the quest at 34th level and had absolutly no problems doing so.  This was back when the quest WAS challanging, pre kunark, back when the sword was a REAL status symbol!  I believe I was one of the first 10 paladins on the rathe to get one.   It takes orginization, good tactics, and friends just like any other quest in EQ.   Granted its not as nice as any of the other weapons out there, but its not supposed to be.   Upgrade to a firey avenger after you get your soulfire, then a firey defender after that.<br><br>The 5 charges of CH alone make me do the quest over and over again.   If they made it rechargeable the weapon would be WAY too over powered unless the quest to recharge it was as difficult, if not more so then the original quest itself.  <br><br>Lucan is a wimp, I have walked into the militia house with one other paladin and a druid to heal me and wiped out everything in there with the exception of the captain.   Just get some high level friends to help you, is very easy.<br><br><br><br>Sir Derek Drygon<br>57th rank Knight of Truth<br>Champions of Norrath<br>The Rathe<br> <p>"Hear it not Heaven thine ministers have done it!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeynsoulfighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyn Soulfighter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/7/01 9:12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3215.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://jbob147.homestead.com/files/keynmug1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Improve SoulFire!</span><hr size=1> but not everyone can just "get their FA... or their FD...<br><br>currently im 3rd in line in my alliance to get the books (already have everything except the sword from the hole for FD)<br><br>and the paladin that is waiting on a Vox book.. has been waiting on one for almost a year an